In my 82 in the thin Colorado altitude I will run 270 in steep long 
climbs, and on one steep climb at 8600 feet hit just under 300.  Head 
temps held just fine at just over 350 for the steep heavy loaded 
climbs.  I noted that at altitudes lower than 5000 my temps on hill 
climbs are lower.
